Package: proTN
Title: Integrative package for the analysis of MS proteomics and phospho-proteomics data
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gabriele", "Tomè", email = "gabriele.tome@unitn.it", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Toma", "Tebaldi", email = "toma.tebaldi@unitn.it", role = "aut"),
	person("Romina", "Belli", role = "aut"),
	person("Daniele", "Peroni", role = "aut"))
Description: proTN is a comprehensive R package designed for the analysis of proteomic and phospho-proteomic datasets. The package offers a collection of functions to process, analyze, and visualize high-throughput data from mass spectrometry experiments. It is particularly tailored to handle both protein-level and peptide-level data, as well as phosphorylation site data, making it highly versatile for various types of proteomics studies. The package integrates multiple key steps of proteomics data analysis into a streamlined workflow, including data normalization, batch effect correction, differential expression analysis, and the generation of informative plots for visualizing results. Whether you're working with a standard proteomic dataset or a more complex phospho-proteomic dataset, proTN provides tools to uncover meaningful biological insights and facilitate data interpretation. proTN is especially useful for researchers conducting large-scale proteomic and phospho-proteomic experiments, as it provides functions that automate many of the routine steps in data preprocessing and analysis. Its ability to handle batch effects ensures that the data you are working with is of high quality, improving the reliability of your results. Additionally, the package makes it easy to visualize complex data through volcano plots and lollipop plots, allowing for quick assessment of significant findings. 
